Why pooled OLS is biased

If we ignore U_i and estimate: 
Y_{it} = \widetilde{\alpha} + \widetilde{\beta}X_{it} + e_{it}

where the composite error term is: 
e_{it} = U_i + \varepsilon_{it}

Then: 
\mathbb{E}[\widetilde\beta]
= \beta + \frac{\text{Cov}(X_{it}, U_i)}{\text{Var}(X_{it})}

